The paper deals with distributed algorithms for computing treewidth, which is a graph parameter related to the structure of the graph. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to graph algorithms and distributed computing. 

cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category, as the paper explicitly deals with distributed algorithms. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category, as treewidth is a graph parameter that is closely related to the structure of the graph, and the paper discusses algorithms for computing it. 

cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category, as treewidth is a graph parameter that is studied in discrete mathematics. 

cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category, as the paper discusses the complexity of computing treewidth and its applications to solving NP-hard problems. 

cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is another possible category, as treewidth is a graph parameter that is used in game theory to analyze the complexity of games on graphs.
